For salsa, in a bowl, combine the carrots, mango, lime juice, chives, 1/8 teaspoon salt, 1/8 teaspoon pepper, coriander and cumin; set aside. Sprinkle tuna steaks with remaining salt and pepper. Coat grill rack with nonstick cooking spray before starting the grill. Grill tuna, covered, over medium heat for 5-7 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Top with salsa.